<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: floppydonkeydick</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-08-11 22:04:46</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Just to clear things up these greaves drop off of Venril Sathir in Karnor's Castle.  The breastplate drops off of Trakanon in Sebilis. VS drops all the kunark class specific greaves and TRAK drops all kunark class specific breastplates.<BR>
<BR>
i know that commenting on the breastplates proc on the greaves page is kinda off topic, but since there is no comments page for the breastplate at this time I might as well contribute to the evergrowing pool of saliva accumulating on your keyboards =)<BR>
<BR>
it would be unwise to dismiss the breastplate as being worthless due to the high cast time on its proc. as someone already commented, it will practically eliminate melee downtime, unfortunately casters will still have to meditate their mana up full. a strategy that could also be used for this breastplates proc in large raids could be a cleric using this BP in conjunction with a lvl 53+ druid or shaman assisting them in healing the tank. essentially the cleric could buddy up with a tank and druid/shaman and could ontinously casting CH from this BP while the druid/shaman watched the tanks health in times of danger and used superior heal when needed. since the gods and dragons rarely divert more then 2 or 3 rounds to continous attacks on a single player in the time span of 10 seconds this "backup priest" idea could be fairly effective.<BR>
<BR>
just my thoughts =P</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
