<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Kinter</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-08-24 18:31:56</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>How's this:<BR>
<BR>
You have this breastplate; you go get yourself a level 50-something ogre warrior.  You tell him to pull blues.  The two of you fight constantly.  As soon as he is in range, you start a CHeal.  As soon as it finishes, you start another.  If you keep him buffed up, you will finish every fight at full mana, ready for more action.  If you're pulling carefully, he will never even be in danger.  Twenty seconds just isn't THAT long, and if you are pulling singletons, you'll be just fine.  You can get zero downtime with tricky battles, and you'll rake in unbelieveable experience, since you only have two people in the group.<BR>
<BR>
I don't consider this breastplate worthless.</font></td></tr></table>
