<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Wardoktor</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-12-05 10:01:30</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Greaves are nice, BP is nicer.  No, Donal's isn't just a category killer, and some might prefer EM, but generally Donal's is a step up.<BR>
<BR>
IF you have WIS maxed, you are always going to want Donal's.  Channeling heals while getting pounded is often the cleric's biggest challenge and the AC upgrade here is huge.  Especially with the added AGI to boot on BP.<BR>
<BR>
The Complete Heal proc on the BP is great.  No you can't use it while running and yes the casting time is too long to heal a tank during a battle, not to mention you are blind while using it and to my knowledge, rooted and helpless (if anyone knows how to stop the proc let me know).  You'd be nuts to use a Donal proc except while the group is recovering.  (I suppose you might, if you were OOM in a close fight, click it on a tank and pray.)   However, it turns into an enormous +mana item, in effect, when you need to cheal a tank or two after a battle is over.<BR>
<BR>
This stuff also looks a lot better than Ethereal Mist IMHO, a very handsome charcoal grey with the tiniest hint of color, maybe red/blue/violet/brown, kind of a warm gunmetal grey.  Especially if you are a small race, EM looks downright silly.<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
